            . I am a <rs id="t18291029-201-viclabel1135" type="occupation">shoemaker</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-201-victim1659 t18291029-201-viclabel1135"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18291029-201-crimeloc1136">Seymour-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-201-crimeloc1136" type="placeName" value="Seymour-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18291029-201-crimeloc1136" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18291029-201-off1133 t18291029-201-crimeloc1136"></join>. On the 10th of September I left my boy in the shop - while I was out these shoes were taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-201-person1661">
                  FRANCIS 
                  KEYS
               <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1661" type="surname" value="KEYS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1661" type="given" value="FRANCIS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1661" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . On the 10th of September I was with Rierdon - we watched the two prisoners for a few minutes - they stopped at a pawnbroker's; West left the other, and went into the shop - I followed him, and saw him with these shoes on the counter; I went to the door, and told Rierdon to go on - he went and took Lilley, who was then going away; I went and asked West where he got the shoes - he said a young man at the door gave them to him to pawn; I asked if he ever saw that young man before - he said No: I took him to the door, and said, "Is this the young man?" he said No; I said,"I saw you in conversation with him" - I took them to the office; I did not know who they belonged to, but I saw the name of E. Driver, Esq. on them, looked in the Court Guide, and found him.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. BARRY. Q. You saw the shoes in the shop? A. Yes - that was the first I saw of them; he denied that Lilley was the person who gave them to him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18291029-201-person1662">
                  DANIEL 
                  RIERDON
               <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1662" type="surname" value="RIERDON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1662" type="given" value="DANIEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1662" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was outside, and took Lilley - I found nothing on him.</p>
               <p>West's Defence. There was nothing but "Driver" on the shoes; I told the officer the person was waiting at the corner of the street, and if he would allow me to go to the corner I should be able to clear myself - he said, "No, I have got you;" in going to the watch-house he said,"Why don't you, like a good lad, say he gave them to you?" I said, "I will not bring an innocent lad into trouble;" the person asked me where the nearest pawnbroker's was - I said I would pawn them; he said pawn them for 5s. in the name of 
               <persName id="t18291029-201-person1663">
                  William 
                  Ring
               <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1663" type="surname" value="Ring"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1663" type="given" value="William"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-person1663" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            , Pancras-street.</p>
               <p>JURY to FRANCIS KEYS. Q. Did he ask you to go to Pancras-street? A. Yes, but I did not, because I had seen him with the other.</p>
               <p>WEST - <rs id="t18291029-201-verdict1137" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18291029-201-verdict1137" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged 19.</p>
